Variation of "the" in French

1) La
   "La" can be use when the word is feminime (check gender-rules)
2) Le
   "Le" used when the word is masculine (also check gender-rules)
3) l'
   if the beginning of the word is started with vocal letter(a,e,i,o,u) and "h",no matter the gender is,le/la must turn to "l'"
   *Example : l'homme ,l'aeroport , l'hotel
